{"questionId":"14295","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A group of 10 girls recorded the number of hours they spent watching television during a particular week. Their results are summarized in the box-and-whisker plot below.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/ac835bb6c479c0b82596c187c199d7d95fba7bf1.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of the interquartile range.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid approach&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; &nbsp; 20 − 15,&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{Q_3} - {Q_1}\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi>Q</mi> <mn>3</mn> </msub> </mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi>Q</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> </mrow> </math></span>,&nbsp; 15&nbsp;− 20</p>\n<p>IQR = 5&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1 N2</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14295","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ2.S_8b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of the interquartile range.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.3—Mean, median, mode. Mean of grouped data, standard deviation. Quartiles, IQR"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}